  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="NL">ACC Laboratory Capacity for COVID-19</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="NL">This proposed project seeks to contribute to the realization of key laboratory components of Ghana&#x2019;s Strategic National COVID-19 Response Plan on quality assurance and data management. Ghana&#x2019;s laboratories, lack efficient and timely COVID-19 data transmission capacity that will facilitate transfer of test results and data with Ministry of Health (MoH), Ghana Health Service (GHS) and hospitals for a timely response. Thus the application will help support the emergency response plan in Ghana by improving testing and detection of the virus. The work will focus on strengthening laboratory diagnosis including: 1. Ensure adherence to safety and quality assurance protocols within COVID-19 testing laboratories as part of national quality assurance program for PCR testing 2. Provide monitoring and onsite technical support for PCR testing to enhance the quality of molecular PCR testing capacity at COVID-19 testing laboratories 3. Enhance the accuracy and efficiency of COVID-19 test results collation and transmission within laboratory departments and to user agencies such as MoH/GHS, COVID-19 isolation/treatment centres and health facilities.</narrative>
  </description>
